==English==

===Etymology===
Latin '''per alia''', by combination, from ''[[per]]'', by or through, and ''alia'', unity, combination.

===Adverb===

# A proposition held to be true because it follows from other true propositions.

"If humans are mortal, and Socrates is a human, then ''per ali'' Socrates is mortal."

====Usage Notes====
Because this is a Latin phrase, it is usually italicized when written.